President Obama has declared a major disaster in Virginia due to severe winter storms and snowstorms that occurred in February 2010. Federal aid will be provided to assist in the recovery efforts in the affected areas. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and emergency protective measures. Hazard mitigation measures will also be funded for the entire Commonwealth. Regis Leo Phelan has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations. Further damage assessments may lead to additional designations and assistance. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.